task.summary: Default task
Added API to get a list of Top 20 companies by capitalisation. Returns JSON list sorted by Market Capitalisation.
Fixed a wrong character in the URL to get Top 20 list

Abstracted the Top 20 list to take a parameter of top 20, 50, 100, 200 and 300 Renamed Controller from Top20Controller to TopASXController. Had to add some checkers for the table selection of Top 200 as there is more information and tables on it than the others.

Added unit tests for getting array of companies in the stock exchange and get a single company code. Single is tested with valid and invalid stock codes. Please note that these tests will not work with the Commands in their current standing, mainly for GetCompany. This is because we have taken the TDD way, so the Commands will have to updated so that the test works.
added registration input fields.
added trading page and accounts page

Updated the UserController to have an API style response/return type for use in AJAX. Updated the API call to be done in the web routes for ease of use. Updated the UserDashboard to call the editUser API and catch errors if they persist, and to change the values of the view fields (name, email etc...) to the values they have been updated to.
Updated some comments on the dashboard to make it easier to understand

Able to create new Trading Accounts when signed in using the form in the dashboard. Trading accounts are now pulled from the DB and properly displayed. Trading account cards are clickable to go to the trading account page. Added comments. Cleaned up redundant code and general maintainance. DB migration now puts a user_id column in the Trade Accounts page that is assigned when a user creates a new Trade Account.
Minor styling changes to the navbar autocomplete search bar suggestions
